## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of historical data and the potential biases in contemporary accounts of the Spanish Flu. The lack of comprehensive economic data from the period makes it challenging to quantify the full economic impact. Additionally, the societal changes attributed to the pandemic may also have been influenced by concurrent events, such as World War I, making it difficult to isolate the effects of the flu alone.